#==============================================================================
# ** Data_Troops
#------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  Contains static data that can't be set in the GUI
#
#  Interview data, nothing more than an array of strings
#  Lines preceeded by @ are Meiko's and shown in different colour
#==============================================================================

$data_interview = []

# === Alex
$data_interview[1] = 
"@Today I'm speaking to one of the druids\n" + 
"@of the Oischin Sacred circle, Alex. \n" + 
"@I'm glad you could join us today, Alex, \n" + 
"@and... What are you doing?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"These plants. They are not getting \n" + 
"enough sunlight. You should put them\n" + 
"closer to the window and give them \n" + 
"more water.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Ah, well, thank you for the tip. Maybe\n" + 
"@we can do this later, so-\n" + 
"\n" + 
"There are many insects here. Have you \n" + 
"been killing all the spiders?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Uhm... I don't really like spiders, \n" + 
"@so I'd rather have flies, thanks.\n" + 
"@Besides, as a druid, shouldn't you be \n" + 
"@protecting all life, even that of \n" + 
"@insects?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"That's not how nature works. If nothing \n" + 
"died, nothing could live. Druids \n" + 
"maintain the balance between life and \n" + 
"death within the forests.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Oh, I see...\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Please take my advice into \n" + 
"consideration. This is not a healthy\n" + 
"place to work. It's suffocating. I need \n" + 
"some fresh air now.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@W-Wait... The rest of the interview...\n" + 
""

# === Angel
$data_interview[2] = 
"@Today I'm interviewing Angel Windsor, \n" + 
"@former Kirgard colonel and childhood\n" + 
"@friend of Daniel Vinyard.\n" + 
"@Miss Windsor, the first thing I wanted\n" + 
"@to ask: having worked so closely with \n" + 
"@Mr. Vinyard and Mr. Knight in the past, \n" + 
"@it must've been tough dealing with \n" + 
"@people with such strong personalities.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"I've grown used to it. I've known them\n" + 
"for so long, it's become normal to me.\n" + 
"They can be difficult at times, but \n" + 
"we're still friends. \n" + 
"\n" + 
"@You joined the army before Daniel did.\n" + 
"@Was it Jovian Knight who convinced you\n" + 
"@to sign up?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Yes, he talked to me about it many \n" + 
"times. He felt very strongly about \n" + 
"fighting Almenga, you see. To him, it \n" + 
"was a fight that concerned everyone,\n" + 
"one that had to be won. If it weren't\n" + 
"for him, I don't think either Daniel\n" + 
"or me would have joined the army.\n" + 
"But... after the war, I do think he felt \n" + 
"guilty about pressuring us to join.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Guilty? \n" + 
"\n" + 
"I think he saw it as just another of his\n" + 
"adventures. Even though we were all \n" + 
"adults, we didn't truly realize what it\n" + 
"meant to fight in a war. There were \n" + 
"times when we almost died, and I think \n" + 
"he felt guilty about that, about putting\n" + 
"his friends' lives in danger. We all \n" + 
"matured a lot during that year.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@I see... but there was still another\n" + 
"@close friend of yours who didn't come\n" + 
"@with you, wasn't there?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Yes... Brunhild was the only one to stay\n" + 
"behind. None of us even considered \n" + 
"asking her. I was raised as a \n" + 
"blacksmith's daughter and spent all my \n" + 
"life around weaponry, but she was\n" + 
"different. She hated fighting, and she\n" + 
"always tried to break up arguments \n" + 
"between us.\n" + 
"When Daniel decided to leave... it was \n" + 
"a difficult time for her. She frequently\n" + 
"sent us letters, always asking if we \n" + 
"were doing fine. I'm sure she was very \n" + 
"lonely during that time. I wonder if...\n" + 
"that was one of the reasons she changed\n" + 
"so much. \n" + 
"\n" + 
"@I can see how that would be tough on\n" + 
"@someone. Thank you for telling us about\n" + 
"@all this.\n" + 
""

# === Avelion
$data_interview[3] = 
"@Today I'm meeting with Avelion, one of\n" + 
"@the most unique members of the Elysium\n" + 
"@army. Is it true that, despite your \n" + 
"@normal appearance, you are actually\n" + 
"@a real dragon?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Indeed, I am a silver dragon. This is\n" + 
"merely a temporary form that allows me\n" + 
"to mingle with humans without \n" + 
"attracting attention.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@It's very fascinating. To us, dragons\n" + 
"@are creatures of legend. I never\n" + 
"@imagined they existed for real. Where\n" + 
"@exactly do you come from?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"A land far, far west of here that has\n" + 
"no name in human language. Few of your\n" + 
"kind exist there, and we have little\n" + 
"contact with them.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@I can't help but wonder after meeting\n" + 
"@you though... are there many more \n" + 
"@dragons among us?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"During our long lives, many of us \n" + 
"venture out from time to time, to learn\n" + 
"from other civilizations and keep watch\n" + 
"on the world around us. They exist even\n" + 
"here, I'm certain, but I could not tell\n" + 
"you how many. I have only recently \n" + 
"arrived in order to hunt down a stray\n" + 
"one.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@You're referring to Tiamat?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Red dragons are a troublesome kind. They\n" + 
"are greedy and selfish. Most of them,\n" + 
"however, keep to themselves. Only few,\n" + 
"like her, actively seek to sow chaos.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Now that Tiamat has been slain, what \n" + 
"@will you do next?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"I've grown curious about the limits of\n" + 
"human strength. I never imagined that\n" + 
"people such as you would be able to \n" + 
"defeat a powerful dragon such as her.\n" + 
"I will spend some time among your kind\n" + 
"in order to better understand humans.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Well, I hope you can learn a lot from\n" + 
"@your stay here, as I've learned a lot\n" + 
"@from you. Thank you for your time.\n" + 
""

# === Ayara
$data_interview[4] = 
"@Today I'm talking to Ayara, one of the\n" + 
"@founding members of the Elysium Army.\n" + 
"@Welcome, Ayara. Now, even though you've\n" + 
"@been playing a large role in the army's\n" + 
"@recent history, we actually know very\n" + 
"@little about your background. What\n" + 
"@were you doing before the war began?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Well, I've really just been in the royal\n" + 
"army. I was a soldier in the third\n" + 
"legion, serving under Colonel Vinyard.\n" + 
"That's how I got to know him. \n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Why did you decide to join the army?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"I don't really know! It's just that...\n" + 
"there didn't seem to be a lot of other\n" + 
"things I could do. I'm not smart enough\n" + 
"to go to school, and I grew up in a \n" + 
"very small town. My father taught me to\n" + 
"hunt, so it wasn't like I couldn't do\n" + 
"anything. Well, one time we were at the\n" + 
"capital when we saw an army parade, and\n" + 
"I thought it looked really amazing.\n" + 
"I just decided at that time that I \n" + 
"wanted to become a part of that.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@I guess things didn't really turn out\n" + 
"@the way you were planning.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"You can say that! I still can't believe\n" + 
"I'm here now. So much has already \n" + 
"happened in such a short time. But I'm\n" + 
"proud of it as well! We've really come \n" + 
"a long way.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@If you could go back to the time when\n" + 
"@you decided to follow Colonel Vinyard,\n" + 
"@would you make the same choice?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Of course! Maybe I would've been safer \n" + 
"if I hadn't come here, but it was worth \n" + 
"it. I know I did the right thing.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@I wasn't expecting anything different.\n" + 
""

# === Bartolli
$data_interview[5] = 
"@Today I'm interviewing Bartolli, owner\n" + 
"@of Elysium castle's general store.\n" + 
"@Welcome, Bartolli. Maybe you could tell\n" + 
"@us a bit about yourself?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Sure, no problem. Bartolli brand goods\n" + 
"are the best you'll find anywhere in\n" + 
"the country. I only supply the highest\n" + 
"quality wares at reasonable prices.\n" + 
"You'll get your groceries for little, \n" + 
"and a smile for free.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@I asked for an introduction, not a \n" + 
"@sales pitch.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Oh, me? Well, what can I say. I'm the\n" + 
"owner of the Bartolli General Market,\n" + 
"formerly in Grunthall, now at Elysium\n" + 
"Castle. I'm a man with a sharp eye for\n" + 
"quality who cares about his customers.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@I'll have to stop you here, or else\n" + 
"@I'd have to charge you for advertising.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Don't forget to drop by, everyone!\n" + 
""

# === Bast
$data_interview[6] = 
"@Today I'm interviewing Bast Gunwood,\n" + 
"@former major in the State Army and\n" + 
"@chief strategist of the Elysium Army.\n" + 
"@Bast, you have a very high reputation\n" + 
"@within both Kirgard and Zelmony. Is it \n" + 
"@true that you've never lost a battle?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Nope, it's not true, and I'm not going\n" + 
"to lie about it. Anyone who claims he's\n" + 
"never lost a battle is either talking\n" + 
"out of his ass or damn lucky. No one's\n" + 
"born a military genius. The best \n" + 
"strategists are the ones who can learn\n" + 
"from their mistakes.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@You retired from the State Army ten\n" + 
"@years ago. What led you to resign?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"If you know anything about the recent\n" + 
"state of Zelmony you'd know already, but\n" + 
"fine. A decade ago we were involved in\n" + 
"a border war in Highland. The Fairwind\n" + 
"Republic tried to encroach on Cayeskan\n" + 
"territory, the Highland army stepped\n" + 
"in to help them, and were in turn \n" + 
"attacked by the Fairwind army. It was\n" + 
"a very messy war. The Matrech Guard was\n" + 
"sent in, and I was senior advisor to the \n" + 
"general in charge. \n" + 
"Well, opinions in Matrech were split.\n" + 
"The chancellor was wary of agitating \n" + 
"a large neighbour like the republic and\n" + 
"wanted to settle the dispute quickly.\n" + 
"Others saw it at a chance to spread \n" + 
"their influence and advocated anything\n" + 
"from annexing Cayeska to actually \n" + 
"invading Fairwind territory. By the way,\n" + 
"one of the champions for the latter \n" + 
"cause was none other than Governor \n" + 
"Vosch.\n" + 
"Anyway, I came up a plan to sweep the \n" + 
"invading army from Cayeska from the\n" + 
"north and take one of their key ports\n" + 
"as a bargaining tool for a settlement.\n" + 
"It all went wrong when politicians in \n" + 
"Matrech started meddling with our \n" + 
"plans. Different factions would send\n" + 
"their people over to review our plans\n" + 
"and try to change our minds. Officers \n" + 
"were removed from the front and \n" + 
"replaced with more 'agreeable' ones.\n" + 
"As a result of all this, army unity was \n" + 
"lost as it dissolved into cliques of\n" + 
"like-minded people more concerned about\n" + 
"furthering their own goals than \n" + 
"following our overall strategy.\n" + 
"Sure, we won the war, and in Matrech it\n" + 
"was spun as a grand victory, but in \n" + 
"truth, it was a disaster. My plans\n" + 
"anticipated a two to three month \n" + 
"campaign. In the end, it took almost\n" + 
"two years, and ravaged the area. \n" + 
"Highland managed okay, but it seriously\n" + 
"strained our relations with Cayeska,\n" + 
"a former part of the Zelmony Kingdom.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@And that's when you decided to leave.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Yep, that's right. Coming back to the\n" + 
"capital and seeing all those people who\n" + 
"were responsible for the chaos celebrate \n" + 
"our victory as if it were their own \n" + 
"doing, I couldn't take it any longer.\n" + 
"I said goodbye and moved away from\n" + 
"everything.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Until Daniel Vinyard came to see you.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"I hope he'll be different, like Ryan\n" + 
"used to be before he lost his real \n" + 
"power. So far, he hasn't disappointed \n" + 
"me. I still have hope.\n" + 
""

# === Beau
$data_interview[7] = 
"@Today I'm speaking with Beau, the \n" + 
"@attorney who defended Mr. Vinyard during \n" + 
"@his trial.\n" + 
"@First of all, a few questions about the \n" + 
"@Zelmony justice system. Military and \n" + 
"@civil cases are treated in the same way, \n" + 
"@right?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Yes, that is correct. However, the \n" + 
"sentence may be different, as in the\n" + 
"former case there is the possibility of \n" + 
"demotion or discharge, but this is up to\n" + 
"the judge.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Have you had earlier experience with \n" + 
"@corruption within the Zelmony justice\n" + 
"@system?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Well, that's a difficult question for \n" + 
"me to answer. Of course there have been \n" + 
"cases where I had my doubts about some \n" + 
"of the evidence produced by the \n" + 
"prosecution, but of course that is not\n" + 
"proof of corruption by itself. I simply \n" + 
"don't have enough information.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@That means the case against Mr. Vinyard \n" + 
"@must've stood out from the rest.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Yes, indeed. I believe there must've \n" + 
"been a certain level of desperation \n" + 
"within the prosecution, or rather, those \n" + 
"who wished to influence the trial. As \n" + 
"such, they felt it necessary to go to \n" + 
"extreme lengths. Once a person has \n" + 
"enemies within the justice system \n" + 
"itself, it will be very hard to get \n" + 
"an unbiased trial.   \n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Yes, I understand. Would you have any\n" + 
"@suggestions on how to improve the\n" + 
"@system?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Well, there are two approaches: from the\n" + 
"bottom up, or from the top down. Lawyers\n" + 
"such as me could do their part by\n" + 
"doing their work properly and reporting \n" + 
"incidents of corruption. In this \n" + 
"situation, however, I believe a\n" + 
"thorough investigation from the top is\n" + 
"necessary to probe those who would \n" + 
"stay out of reach otherwise. This is no\n" + 
"light matter, and would take a very \n" + 
"dedicated commission with a clear \n" + 
"mandate. It's probably impossible in \n" + 
"the current political climate, but \n" + 
"still, I have good hopes for the \n" + 
"future.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@I share your hopes, Beau. Maybe getting\n" + 
"@all of this out in the open will \n" + 
"@finally trigger a reaction.\n" + 
"@Thank you for your time.\n" + 
""

# === Bruce
$data_interview[8] = 
"@Today I'm talking to Bruce Erickson,\n" + 
"@a Kirgard colonel who has served under\n" + 
"@General Keyser and General Leonius.\n" + 
"@Colonel Erickson, you've known Daniel\n" + 
"@Vinyard for a long time, haven't you?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Yeah. Unfortunately.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Your relation with him was not very\n" + 
"@good I see.\n" + 
" \n" + 
"Of course not! We served together, \n" + 
"that's all we have in common. He's been \n" + 
"a thorn in my side all along. If it \n" + 
"weren't for him, -I- would've been a \n" + 
"general now instead of Knight.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@How so?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"During the last war, I was first in line \n" + 
"to get promoted, but Daniel couldn't \n" + 
"take it and thought he deserved it more.\n" + 
"Because he tried to discredit me, I was\n" + 
"passed over. That little incident hurt\n" + 
"my chances for years afterwards. I was \n" + 
"still made a colonel despite all that,\n" + 
"so imagine if he hadn't stood in my way\n" + 
"back then. \n" + 
"\n" + 
"@That's... a pretty long time to hold\n" + 
"@a grudge.\n" + 
""

# === Carson 
$data_interview[9] = 
"@Today I'm meeting with Carson, private \n" + 
"@aide to Chancellor Ryan of Zelmony and \n" + 
"@currently a member of the Elysium army.\n" + 
"@Carson, even though you're young, you \n" + 
"@seem to have a pretty important \n" + 
"@position, don't you?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"My official tasks include delivering \n" + 
"messages from and to the chancellor, \n" + 
"writing down notes and speeches, and \n" + 
"gathering information when he's unable \n" + 
"to. How important my work is depends \n" + 
"completely on what the chancellor asks \n" + 
"of me.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Still, he seems to trust you a lot. \n" + 
"@First of all, how did you end up in your \n" + 
"@position?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"I was just lucky. My father was an \n" + 
"administrator there who had occasional \n" + 
"contact with the chancellor. I was only \n" + 
"twelve when he suddenly died, and since \n" + 
"he was well-liked in Matrech, they gave \n" + 
"me a job as messenger so I could help \n" + 
"support my family. I have a good memory \n" + 
"and it turned out I also have a keen ear \n" + 
"for what people around me are talking \n" + 
"about, so after a few years the \n" + 
"chancellor asked me to become his aide.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@When you describe your tasks,\n" + 
"@gathering information in particular,\n" + 
"@you sort of represent the chancellor\n" + 
"@himself. Does that mean some people \n" + 
"@are reluctant to talk to you?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Of course. Everyone in Matrech knows who \n" + 
"I am, and they know that everything they \n" + 
"say to me will reach the chancellor. One \n" + 
"of the first things you learn is how to \n" + 
"get information out of people who're not \n" + 
"willing to give it to you. \n" + 
"\n" + 
"@It probably also gives you some standing \n" + 
"@among government officials.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Yes, it's best that they don't insult \n" + 
"me either.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@When you think about it, you almost \n" + 
"@sound like a spy for the chancellor.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"There are certain things I can't talk \n" + 
"about.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@One last thing. What are your \n" + 
"@aspirations for the future? \n" + 
"\n" + 
"It's hard to say. The whole future of \n" + 
"the country is uncertain at this point.\n" + 
"For now, I'll keep studying and building\n" + 
"a network of connections for future use.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@I see. Well, good luck with that, and\n" + 
"@thank you for your time.\n" + 
""

# === Cid
$data_interview[10] = 
"@Today I'm meeting with Cid, a bard and\n" + 
"@poet. Welcome, Cid.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Ah, it's a pleasure to be here.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Now, I've heard you recently wrote \n" + 
"@something you described as your \n" + 
"@masterpiece. Have you been performing\n" + 
"@it yet?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"I have, yes. To small audiences, so far,\n" + 
"but I'm certain as word spreads that\n" + 
"larger crowds will soon flock to my\n" + 
"recitals.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@How have the reactions been so far?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"I'm sure that people were deeply moved\n" + 
"by my wonderful music.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@You're sure? Well... haven't you \n" + 
"@actually asked anyone about it?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Ask? Oh, no no. Art is an experience,\n" + 
"a feeling. I can't just simply ask \n" + 
"people if they thought it was good. They\n" + 
"may not even realize on a conscious\n" + 
"level how affected they've been.\n" + 
" \n" + 
"@I... see. Well, I'm glad you were able\n" + 
"@to... enlighten us.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Oh no, the pleasure was all mine.\n" + 
"Perhaps in return you would like to \n" + 
"hear my latest work?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Another time, maybe.\n" + 
""

# === Col
$data_interview[11] = 
"@Today I'm interviewing Col, a young\n" + 
"@soldier from the Mayfall Army.\n" + 
"@Col, you were the first Zelmonian to\n" + 
"@join the Elysium Army. What led you to\n" + 
"@make that transfer?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"I don't really know exactly. It was just\n" + 
"a feeling. I had to escort Mr. Vinyard\n" + 
"to Matrech so we traveled together for\n" + 
"a while, and I was really impressed by\n" + 
"his kindness and confidence. When I \n" + 
"heard he was being given his own unit,\n" + 
"I knew I had to join it.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Are you still happy with that \n" + 
"@decision?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Yes! I am! I can't imagine what all \n" + 
"these recent events would've been like\n" + 
"if I'd still been in the Mayfall Army,\n" + 
"but here, even though we have to fight\n" + 
"so hard, I still feel safe as long as\n" + 
"we're all together.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@You've been here since the beginning\n" + 
"@and you must've seen a lot of new \n" + 
"@people arrive. Who among the army do\n" + 
"@you get along with the most?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"I like Ayara. She's really strong but\n" + 
"also nice to everyone. I wish I could\n" + 
"be more like her. \n" + 
"I get along with Carson pretty well too, \n" + 
"but... he seems much more mature, even\n" + 
"though we're almost the same age. I \n" + 
"don't really know what he's thinking \n" + 
"most of the time. \n" + 
"\n" + 
"@I see, very interesting. Well, Col,\n" + 
"@thank you for your time.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"No problem!\n" + 
""

# === Daniel
$data_interview[12] = 
"@Today I am speaking to none other than \n" + 
"@the commander of the Elysium army \n" + 
"@himself, Daniel Vinyard.\n" + 
"@Mr. Vinyard, I'm very glad you could \n" + 
"@spare some time for me. It's a great \n" + 
"@honour. You must be a very busy man.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"I certainly don't get bored around \n" + 
"here, but on the other hand, there are \n" + 
"many talented people here who take care \n" + 
"of the day-to-day operation of the army. \n" + 
"Without them, the whole structure would \n" + 
"fall apart instantly. Compared to that, \n" + 
"my efforts are only modest.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@But it's you who inspired all these \n" + 
"@people to work together, isn't it? \n" + 
"@So you could say that everyone here \n" + 
"@is indispensable, including you.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"That's a good way of putting it, yes. \n" + 
"Everyone has their own role.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@A statement that seems to match your \n" + 
"@views well...\n" + 
"@During my preparations for this \n" + 
"@interview, I found that few people had \n" + 
"@any specific questions they'd like to \n" + 
"@ask you, personal ones at least. It \n" + 
"@looks like everyone appreciates your \n" + 
"@openness in general.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"I'm glad to hear that. There were no \n" + 
"questions that showed up frequently?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Well... One that popped up a few times\n" + 
"@times was, \"are you single?\".\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Haha... I'll admit the answer to that\n" + 
"is \"Yes\", but I don't think this is \n" + 
"the time or place to do something about \n" + 
"that. I guess I'm currently engaged to \n" + 
"my work.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Well, in that case, I won't take up \n" + 
"@any more of your valuable time. Thank\n" + 
"@you, Mr. Vinyard.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"No problem.\n" + 
""

# === Darwin
$data_interview[13] = 
"@Today I'm meeting with Darwin, a \n" + 
"@student from Faraday University.\n" + 
"@Darwin, you are a scholar in the \n" + 
"@magical arts, correct?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"That's the official title yes, but I\n" + 
"prefer not to use that preposterous\n" + 
"name. This is not some kind of art,\n" + 
"it's a hard science, and therefore it\n" + 
"deserves to be called magical science.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@But is it really a science the way that\n" + 
"@physics is?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Of course it is. It's the study of a\n" + 
"natural phenomenon. It's governed by\n" + 
"laws just like everything else in the\n" + 
"world around us. \n" + 
"\n" + 
"@And that's what you're doing at Faraday\n" + 
"@University?\n" + 
"\n" + 
