# === Jasper
$data_interview[27] = 
"@Today I'm meeting with Jasper, one of\n" + 
"@the Knights of Matrech.\n" + 
"@Jasper, maybe you could start by \n" + 
"@explaining exactly what the Knights of \n" + 
"@Matrech are, and how they fit into the \n" + 
"@Matrech Guard.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Both of them originated in the Zelmony\n" + 
"Kingdom. Matrech was the capital of the \n" + 
"kingdom, and so the Matrech Guard were \n" + 
"the main force, setting them apart from \n" + 
"vassal armies. The name remained after \n" + 
"the kingdom split up, and is now still \n" + 
"in use for the Matrech army.\n" + 
"Within the original Matrech Guard, \n" + 
"the Knights of Matrech were the elite\n" + 
"troops consisting of high nobility. \n" + 
"Their main function was to protect the\n" + 
"capital and the royal family.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@But nowadays it's slightly different, \n" + 
"@isn't it?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Yes. Despite the name, the Knights of\n" + 
"Matrech are now separate from the \n" + 
"Matrech army. Together with the Captain \n" + 
"of the Matrech Guard, they form the \n" + 
"backbone of the State Army, and it's \n" + 
"their task to coordinate actions between \n" + 
"all states. \n" + 
"\n" + 
"@So the Matrech Guard is simply Matrech's \n" + 
"@own army, but the Knights of Matrech \n" + 
"@serve the State Union as a whole.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Exactly. Local commanders will never be \n" + 
"put in charge of divisions from other \n" + 
"states, but the Knights of Matrech may\n" + 
"be.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@I see. What's your current function \n" + 
"@within the Knights, then?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"I'm still a low-ranking officer. At the \n" + 
"moment, I serve as one of the captain's\n" + 
"personal guards. Normally, I protect her \n" + 
"when she's on a mission, but I may also \n" + 
"be dispatched in her place to deal with \n" + 
"minor affairs, like with the liberation \n" + 
"of Grunthall.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Very interesting. Thank you for your\n" + 
"@explanation.\n" + 
""

