"@gambling business?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"It's not a pretty story. When I was a \n" + 
"young man, I liked to live large and\n" + 
"party a lot. Gambling was the only way \n" + 
"to make enough money for kids like me. \n" + 
"\n" + 
"@By the looks of it, you were pretty\n" + 
"@successful.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"For every guy who wins big, there's \n" + 
"someone else who lost big. If you don't \n" + 
"get good at it fast, you'll run yourself \n" + 
"into debts you can't pay off.\n" + 
"But later, once I was making a decent \n" + 
"living, I started doing it more for the\n" + 
"thrill than the cash. \n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Have you ever had to cheat to survive?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"I did some stupid things when I was \n" + 
"younger, but nowadays I'm all straight. \n" + 
"Let me tell you, in this business, you \n" + 
"get caught once and it's all over. \n" + 
"There are swindlers who can pull it off, \n" + 
"but it's not worth it. You lose a bet,\n" + 
"you can try again. You're caught \n" + 
"cheating, no one will play you again, \n" + 
"if you don't find a noose around your \n" + 
"neck first.\n" + 
"But enough about me, let's talk about \n" + 
"you. You must meet a lot of interesting\n" + 
"people.\n" + 
"\n" + 
