"@Today I'm talking to Merrick, colonel\n" + 
"@of the Mayfall army.\n" + 
"@Colonel, I've heard stories that you\n" + 
"@haven't been on very good footing with\n" + 
"@the State government lately. Is that\n" + 
"@true?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Oh, you think I wasn't on good footing \n" + 
"with a bunch of complete idiots? \n" + 
"What ever could make you think so?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@So it's true, then? What exactly was\n" + 
"@causing this friction?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Mayfall is my home, it's my duty to\n" + 
"protect it, but they? They just treat\n" + 
"it like it was some kind of tool you\n" + 
"can use when you need it and throw\n" + 
"away when you're done. To them it's \n" + 
"just a convenient buffer zone to shield \n" + 
"Matrech from Kirgard.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Surely that's not completely true.\n" + 
"@After all, the State Union put a lot of\n" + 
"@effort into taking back Mayfall after\n" + 
"@General Keyser's invasion.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"For their own security I'm sure. Did you\n" + 
"forget why I'm here now? They threw away\n" + 
"Mayfall because they wanted to get their\n" + 
"grubby hands on Highland again. Well,\n" + 
"screw them! I'm done with all this\n" + 
"bullshit!\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Uh, let's take a break, because I'm\n" + 
"@getting worried about your health.\n" + 
""

