"us in the past. At the moment there is\n" + 
"an uneasy peace, but no one knows how \n" + 
"long it will last. The khan is \n" + 
"maintaining a neutral position as not\n" + 
"to offend either country.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@And yet, you've clearly chosen a side \n" + 
"@in this conflict.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"This was also the khan's decision. \n" + 
"Gojistan and its neighbours have never \n" + 
"had much contact with this continent. \n" + 
"With the dawn of a new age for these\n" + 
