$data_interview[50] = 
"@Today I'm meeting with Outsider, the \n" + 
"@mercenary captain currently in service \n" + 
"@with Elysium.\n" + 
"@So, I call you a mercenary captain, but\n" + 
"@you don't actually have anyone working\n" + 
"@under you, do you?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Nope, I work alone. Some people prefer\n" + 
"calling me a 'strategy consultant', or \n" + 
"something like that. They hire me to \n" + 
"train their own men and lead them in\n" + 
"battle.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Isn't that a little strange? Didn't \n" + 
"@you use to lead an actual mercenary\n" + 
"@army?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"At first, yeah. You see, I used to be a \n" + 
"sergeant in the State Army, but I had \n" + 
"enough of being told what to do, so I \n" + 
"left, and a bunch of my men followed me. \n" + 
"It worked well for a while, but it's a \n" + 
"lot of people to feed and take care of, \n" + 
"and I couldn't always keep them \n" + 
"together. It's much easier this way. \n" + 
"My rates are lower, it's less stressful, \n" + 
"and I still make a better living.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Speaking of feeding, I heard some \n" + 
"@rumours that in your spare time, you \n" + 
"@enjoy cooking. Is that true?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Surprised? A man fights twice as hard if\n" + 
"he's had a good meal. I couldn't rely on \n" + 
"cooks everywhere I went, so I taught \n" + 
"myself how to properly prepare food. \n" + 
"It's a good way to relax. \n" + 
"\n" + 
"@One more thing. What about this other \n" + 
"@mercenary, Mike? What's your relation \n" + 
"@to him?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Mike... He's one of the kids I trained. \n" + 
"It was a job in Highland two years ago. \n" + 
"A local businessman hired me to teach \n" + 
"the mine workers to defend themselves, \n" + 
"against robbers and such. Mike was just \n" + 
"one of the workers there, but he picked \n" + 
"things up from me at amazing speed. He's\n" + 
"a natural. Afterwards, he wanted to come \n" + 
"with me, but I didn't want to drag \n" + 
"anyone else along with me anymore. Well, \n" + 
"the kid insisted, so in the end we \n" + 
"became partners instead. We work \n" + 
"together or separately, but we'll never \n" + 
"work against each other.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@I see. Very interesting. Thank you for\n" + 
"@your time, Outsider.\n" + 
""

