# === Reod
$data_interview[53] = 
"@Today I'm interviewing Reod, a \n" + 
"@rather troublesome mage.\n" + 
"@Now, from a brief investigation of your \n" + 
"@recent past, it seems you've made a lot \n" + 
"@of enemies. Apparently, 'Reod' is just \n" + 
"@one of many different names you've been \n" + 
"@using over the years.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Well, hehe... I guess that's true. I \n" + 
"don't really like to stay in one place \n" + 
"for long.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@You've been arrested before for theft \n" + 
"@and fraud in St. Reinard, Trarcia, \n" + 
"@Blackwater and Harlinton, and in \n" + 
"@addition to that there are several \n" + 
"@loansharks looking out for you.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"You... You didn't tell them I'm here, \n" + 
"right? They think I'm dead, you see. \n" + 
"Well, most of them do. I... I really \n" + 
"don't want to get into even more \n" + 
"trouble.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Don't worry. I've only been gathering \n" + 
"@information, not handing it out. \n" + 
"@Now, how did you manage to get yourself \n" + 
"@into this situation? What are you \n" + 
"@spending all this money on?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Well... t-to tell you the truth, it's... \n" + 
"it's not really for me. I have a little \n" + 
"brother back home. I don't want to tell \n" + 
"you where, but... he's sick, and he \n" + 
"needs expensive medicine. I... don't \n" + 
"really care if I have to live like \n" + 
"this, as long as he's well.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@I see... This does match the story \n" + 
"@you've told a few other people in the \n" + 
"@past. Except that you told them it was \n" + 
"@your sister. And your mother.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"I... I did...?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Yes, you did. Maybe we should end the \n" + 
"@interview here.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"O... Okay.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@And give me back my pencils.\n" + 
""

# === Richard
$data_interview[54] = 
"@Today I'm talking to Richard, a ranger\n" + 
"@who takes care of Mayfall forest.\n" + 
"@Richard, you're paid for doing this\n" + 
"@job by the Mayfall state government,\n" + 
"@right? What exactly is your official\n" + 
"@task? Surely you don't get something\n" + 
"@like the mist problem often.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"No, I'm glad I don't! Usually it's the\n" + 
"basic stuff, keeping track of animal\n" + 
"populations and ensuring the roads are\n" + 
"clear for travellers. A lot of business\n" + 
"between Mayfall and Matrech goes through\n" + 
"my part of the woods.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@I noticed the forest hasn't the safest\n" + 
"@place to travel through lately. Is that\n" + 
"@also due to the mist issue?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Unfortunately yeah. The mist monsters\n" + 
"were a real danger, so I was focusing\n" + 
"all my attention on keeping them away\n" + 
"from the paths. Most caravans have\n" + 
"bodyguards with them anyway, so the \n" + 
"lesser beasts aren't as much of a \n" + 
"problem. I've got a lot of work waiting\n" + 
"for me when I get back though. It's \n" + 
"almost as if this is a vacation for \n" + 
"me, haha.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Hope it doesn't end to soon, then!\n" + 
""

# === Rock
$data_interview[55] = 
"@Today I'm talking to Rock, formerly \n" + 
"@leader of the Highland rebel army and\n" + 
"@now leader of the Highland Republic.\n" + 
"@Now, you've become pretty famous \n" + 
"@lately, but we don't know much about\n" + 
"@your earlier life. How did you get\n" + 
"@involved in the Highland rebellion?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"I used to be a lieutenant in the \n" + 
"Highland Army. I was one of the many\n" + 
"people who couldn't see what was right\n" + 
"in front of them. For years, I believed\n" + 
"the same thing as the people in Matrech\n" + 
"did, that everything's fine, just a few\n" + 
"isolated incidents. The man who changed\n" + 
"me was Joshua's father. He was a \n" + 
"businessman, so he suffered directly\n" + 
"from the corruption. He opened my eyes\n" + 
"and showed me what was really going on\n" + 
"around me. And for that, he was \n" + 
"murdered.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@I heard about this story. You tried to\n" + 
"@expose a corrupt army captain. I see\n" + 
"@why you'd leave the army after that,\n" + 
"@but did you join the rebellion right\n" + 
"@after that?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Joshua told me about a friend of his\n" + 
"father's. You gotta know that at the \n" + 
"time, the rebel army was nothing. An\n" + 
"uprising a year earlier was crushed\n" + 
"mercilessly and not much of it was left.\n" + 
"But this friend was one of the ex-\n" + 
"soldiers who took part in that \n" + 
"uprising, and I went to find him looking\n" + 
"for help. We'd tried playing by the \n" + 
"rules, but the rules were only there to\n" + 
"keep the same people in power. At that\n" + 
"point, I just wanted revenge. Well, I \n" + 
"found the guy, a bunch locals joined up \n" + 
"with us, and that's how it all got \n" + 
"started. He died fighting for control \n" + 
"of the town, but we won in the end, and \n" + 
"from then on, I was in charge of the \n" + 
"main resistance army.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@So the whole rebel army in its current\n" + 
"@form was your own work?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Pretty much. Over the years we merged\n" + 
"with some other more or less successful\n" + 
"rebel organisations, but we were the \n" + 
"first ones to pose a real threat to the\n" + 
"Highland government.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Just one final question: what was your\n" + 
"@relation to Erin back then?\n" + 
"\n" + 
