# === Ryan
$data_interview[58] = 
"@Today I'm meeting with Charles Ryan,\n" + 
"@founder of the Zelmony State Union and\n" + 
"@former chancellor.\n" + 
"@Welcome, Mr. Ryan. It's great honour\n" + 
"@to have you here. Now, as I'm sure you\n" + 
"@can imagine I have an endless list of\n" + 
"@questions to ask you, but I'll try to\n" + 
"@keep this short.\n" + 
"@First of all, I'm interested in your\n" + 
"@rise to power. Is it true you were\n" + 
"@once arrested for disturbing public\n" + 
"@order?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Yes, it's true. My dreams of a unified\n" + 
"Zelmony were not shared by those in \n" + 
"power at the time. As I grew frustrated\n" + 
"with their shortsightedness, I instead\n" + 
"traveled around the country and tried\n" + 
"to appeal to the people instead.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@And this was not appreciated by the\n" + 
"@government?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"At first they saw me as a mere nuisance.\n" + 
"I was only a captain in the army and I\n" + 
"had few connections. But my journey \n" + 
"turned out to be more successful than\n" + 
"anyone had expected, and I gained more \n" + 
"and more followers among the people, in \n" + 
"all levels of society. Many of them felt \n" + 
"insecure and had little faith in their \n" + 
"leaders. However, the overwhelming \n" + 
"support I was enjoying at the time made\n" + 
"me overconfident, and I returned to\n" + 
"Matrech to make my case again, under\n" + 
"the assumption that they could no \n" + 
"longer ignore me. I was right about \n" + 
"that, of course, but I was not expecting\n" + 
"such a negative reaction.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@You were advocating a different kind of\n" + 
"@government at the time, but were you\n" + 
"@actively seeking power yourself?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"I can't deny that I was hoping to be\n" + 
"given a position of influence, but I was\n" + 
"careful about what I said in public.\n" + 
"Moreover, I was never expecting to\n" + 
"actually become chancellor myself.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Anyway, this is where you were \n" + 
"@arrested, right?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Yes. After giving a speech to a large\n" + 
"crowd on the streets of Matrech, the\n" + 
"governor immediately ordered my arrest.\n" + 
"I was shocked, to be honest. With the\n" + 
"benefit of hindsight I can say that it\n" + 
"should have been obvious, but I was\n" + 
"young, and I had come to believe that\n" + 
"if I explained my views properly, \n" + 
"everyone would accept them.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@But in the end, this event was what\n" + 
"@triggered a revolution.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"From my point of view, it all happened\n" + 
"very quickly. From my cell, I heard \n" + 
"little about what was going on outside,\n" + 
"until one day I was told that the\n" + 
"governor of Matrech had stepped down \n" + 
"after a large uprising and that the\n" + 
"people had demanded me to be freed. \n" + 
"\n" + 
"@That must've been an incredible moment.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Yes... After fighting on my own for so\n" + 
"long against what seemed unsurmountable \n" + 
"obstacles, to see such strong support \n" + 
"for my dreams, to see all my work \n" + 
"redeemed... That is a moment I will\n" + 
"never forget.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@I think it's very intriguing, and an\n" + 
"@important event in history to be sure.\n" + 
"@However, I can't help but notice a lot \n" + 
"@of similarities with the present \n" + 
"@situation. A largely complacent \n" + 
"@government, harbouring a strong sense\n" + 
"@of distrust for its neighbours...\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Sadly, that it what the State Union had\n" + 
"come to in the end. Due to the nature of\n" + 
"the new country, control over Zelmony\n" + 
"has slowly slipped away from me. I am\n" + 
"to blame for letting it come this far\n" + 
"as well. I should have stepped down in\n" + 
"favour of a younger, more driven \n" + 
"chancellor long ago. It was too late for\n" + 
"me, but I sincerely hope that Daniel\n" + 
"Vinyard can do for both our countries\n" + 
"what I tried to do for Zelmony.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@I'm certain we're all hoping for the\n" + 
"@same thing. Thank you very much for \n" + 
"@your time, Ryan.\n" + 
""

