# === Stromgaard
$data_interview[66] = 
"@Today I'm speaking to Stromgaard, \n" + 
"@an adventurer. \n" + 
"@Adventurer, that's a vague description, \n" + 
"@isn't it? I understand you travel a lot, \n" + 
"@but what is it that you really do?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"It's a good question. Mostly, I just \n" + 
"wander around until I've found an \n" + 
"interesting place I haven't seen before\n" + 
"yet, and stay there for a while, like \n" + 
"I'm doing now. Sometimes, when I get a \n" + 
"good lead, I like chasing after lost \n" + 
"treasures, but usually I don't really \n" + 
"have a particular goal in mind.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@How did this get started? What made you\n" + 
"@decide to go out and see the world?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Well, I guess it's in my blood. I come \n" + 
"from the Hazan tribe. They're nomads who \n" + 
"used to live on the northern Almengan \n" + 
"plains. From an early age I learned how\n" + 
"to take care of myself and survive in \n" + 
"the wild.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@The Hazan? Oh, I've heard of them. \n" + 
"@Weren't they nearly wiped out during a \n" + 
"@war with Almenga, about a decade ago?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"It was eight years ago, but yeah. The \n" + 
"imperial army destroyed most of our \n" + 
"settlements, and many of us died. I\n" + 
"don't think many of our people still \n" + 
"live a nomadic life nowadays. Most of \n" + 
"them now live as second-class citizens\n" + 
"in Almengan cities. It's one reason I \n" + 
"decided to spend my life traveling. \n" + 
"I was already abroad at the time the \n" + 
"war broke out, but after that, I had \n" + 
"no reason to go back anymore.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@I see... I'm sorry to hear about that. \n" + 
"@I should do more research on this war. \n" + 
"@Anyway, thank you for your time. \n" + 
""

