# === Wilona
$data_interview[73] = 
"@Today I am speaking to our resident \n" + 
"@statistician, Wilona. Thank you for \n" + 
"@sparing some time for us.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Yes, I have reserved 31 minutes and 18 \n" + 
"seconds for this interview.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@You certainly like numbers. Where did \n" + 
"@this all start? What sparked your \n" + 
"@interest in statistics?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"That would be 26 years, 12 days and 7 \n" + 
"hours ago, when I was a young child. \n" + 
"I was at a market, waiting while my\n" + 
"mother was speaking to a friend. It took\n" + 
"so long, I started counting the rice in\n" + 
"a bag she had just bought.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@You counted all the rice?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Yes, there were 35,230 grains in total. \n" + 
"After that, I started counting \n" + 
"everything around me, and suddenly the \n" + 
"most wonderful patterns jumped out. \n" + 
"Once you begin seeing the world in \n" + 
"numbers, it becomes obvious that \n" + 
"everything is related to everything \n" + 
"else. For example, this is the 106th \n" + 
"word I've said to you so far in this \n" + 
"interview, out of the 4312 I say on an \n" + 
"average day. If we're now halfway \n" + 
"through the interview, that means that \n" + 
"it amounts to 4.9% of my daily speech. \n" + 
"If we had this conversation every day \n" + 
"over the span of a year, then I would\n" + 
"have said a total of 77,380 words to\n" + 
"you.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@I see. That's... very interesting.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"If you're interested, please come see \n" + 
"me some time. There are so many other \n" + 
"amazing things I could tell you about. \n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Thank you for the offer, but I'm not \n" + 
"@sure if it would help improve my \n" + 
"@reporting...\n" + 
""

