# === Yomiko
$data_interview[75] = 
"@Today I'm speaking with Yomiko, one of \n" + 
"@the last remaining members of the Sun \n" + 
"@Clan. \n" + 
"@Yomiko, I know your village was heavily \n" + 
"@damaged in the raid by the Shadow Clan, \n" + 
"@but what exactly is its present \n" + 
"@condition? Are there any people left \n" + 
"@there?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Oh, yes. Most of our strongest fighters \n" + 
"were killed, but there were still enough\n" + 
"people to rebuild part of the village. \n" + 
"We weren't strong enough to save Master, \n" + 
"though...\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@I'm curious, where is this village \n" + 
"@located? I've not been able to find out\n" + 
"@anything about it.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"I can't tell you. It's a secret.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@I see, that's a shame. \n" + 
"@You mentioned that the village is being \n" + 
"@rebuilt. How is that going? It must be \n" + 
"@difficult finding the right tools and \n" + 
"@materials when you're living in a forest\n" + 
"@far away from the city.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"We make most of our tools ourselves, so \n" + 
"it's not a problem. There's a lot of \n" + 
"skilled craftsmen among us.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@I see, very interesting. So the village\n" + 
"@is indeed in a forest, far away from \n" + 
"@the city.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"W-What? I didn't say that! I was just \n" + 
"answering the question! It could be \n" + 
"anywhere!\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Okay, different question. Since the \n" + 
"@location of your village is a secret, \n" + 
"@did the Almenga invasion cause any \n" + 
"@trouble for you? \n" + 
"\n" + 
"Huh? Well, it was hard for the people \n" + 
"around us, but we're self-sufficient. \n" + 
"A few times we had to take out groups \n" + 
"of soldiers that were coming too close, \n" + 
"but that's no problem for us.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@I'm also looking for any accounts of \n" + 
"@the battle for the bridges over the \n" + 
"@Fafnir river, including Ft. Brahma. Did \n" + 
"@the imperial army surprise the defenders \n" + 
"@and take it with ease, or was there a \n" + 
"@fierce battle there? Were you already \n" + 
"@aware of the invasion at that point?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"I don't know... When we first found out \n" + 
"about it, the bridges were already\n" + 
"taken.\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@Very interesting. That means the \n" + 
"@village must be north of the river, \n" + 
"@then?\n" + 
"\n" + 
"Stop it! I'm not talking to you anymore! \n" + 
"If Master finds out about this, I'm in\n" + 
"big trouble!\n" + 
"\n" + 
"@I'll take that as a yes.	\n" + 
""

